**Please adhere to the following items in the list**:

* The PR title follows the format <https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0-beta.2/#summary>
* The commit message title follows the format <https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0-beta.2/#summary>
* The PR title is no longer than 76 characters
* The commit message title is no longer than 76 characters
* The first PR comment (this one) is wrapped at 76 characters unless it's really needed
* The first PR comment (this one) clearly describes what it does and why we need it
* A new Template or updates to an existing one should be followed
  by calling `make generate-all` to ensure proper updates;
  any updates in configurations of an existing template require
  to bump its version in the corresponding `Chart.yaml` file;
  corresponding changes should be reflected in the `config/dev` directory
* A reference to a corresponding issue to be fixed or updated
  added via either `Fixes #1234` or `Updates #1234` (the latter if this is not a complete fix)
* If referring to a repo other than `k0rdent/kcm` add the `owner/repo#issue_number` syntax:
  `Fixes k0rdent/kof#1234`
* Fixes or updates to issues might be chained: `Fixes #1234, fixes #1235`
* Delete these instructions once you have read and applied them
